    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-09-17T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-09-17T12:00:00-05:00" n="783"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d783">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1575</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_WJE1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Willard</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-09-17T13:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 17, 1918, 1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1565. Embassy’s 1776, September 5, 1 p.m. Department is inclined to doubt the
                    wisdom of your intimating to Spanish Government that War Trade Board may
                    discontinue its practice in excepting Spanish vessels from bunker negotiations.
                    In view of the satisfactory financial agreement which has just been concluded,
                    it is felt that such an intimation of intention to exert further pressure might
                    not be well <pb facs="0891" n="1725" xml:id="pg_1725"/> received even though the
                    intimation is only made for the purpose of later withdrawing it. Your further
                    views are desired.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
